feat: rewrite as gesetze_corpus package with two-repo data split

Restructure the tools repository into a proper Python package
(gesetze_corpus) with pinned dependencies, a CLI (python -m
gesetze_corpus) and clean module boundaries: http, fetch, parse,
canonical, render, ingest, events, util.

Canonicalization v1 is frozen (docs/CANONICAL.md): NFC text, XML c14n2,
sorted JSON with LF endings. The parser is reimplemented on lxml and
fixes three bugs from the previous scripts/ pipeline (double paragraph
sign in headings, duplicated Absatz prefix, over-aggressive norm
filter).

Laws are now emitted into a separate data repository
(../gesetze-corpus-data) under laws/<BJNR>/{source.xml, meta.json,
toc.json, paragraphs/, annexes/} with per-paragraph markdown files.
The initial snapshot holds the full current state; future commits
will carry per-effective-date changes.

Adds unit tests for canonical text, canonical XML, slug padding,
xml parser and markdown renderer, plus a CI workflow and a scaffolded
daily-snapshot workflow that pushes to the data repo.
